-- Q-Cells Climbs in Frankfurt Trading on Early Loan Repayment Announcement
-- Zoe Schneeweiss
-- 2010-09-20T07:05:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/q-cells-gains-5-2-after-saying-ldk-solar-to-repay-225-million-loan-early.html

          
          
             Q-Cells SE, a German photovoltaic
company, rose as much as 5.2 percent in Frankfurt trading after
announcing that it has reached an agreement with LDK Solar of
China to repay the loan extended to LDK Solar by Q-Cells in 2008
early and to adjust the existing solar wafer supply contract.  
 Shares rose as much as 27 cents to 5.51 euros and was
trading at 5.451 euros at 9:05 a.m. in Frankfurt.  
 Q-Cells said the $224.9 million loan will be repaid by the
end of 2011, the company said in a statement today.  
          
          


  


        